<module status="bronze">
    <h>seòl</h>
    <p><g>seòl</g>
        <en>sail</en> is a <a href="?xx=verbs/simple_verbs">simple verb</a>, denoting an event/activity of <a
            href="?q=motion">manner of motion</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>seòl</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>seòlaidh</m> – future independent, i.e. <en>will sail</en></li>
                <li><m>sheòl</m> – past independent, i.e. <en>sailed</en></li>
                <li><m>seòladh</m> – verbal noun, i.e. <en>sailing</en></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
